@@@Add a git remote in the Cloud9 console. Should look like this (replace the git url with your repo url):

1.Create a new git in github

2. git remote add origin git@github.com:C9Support/testPush.git 

3.Add files and commit them:
git add . 
git commit -m "First commit"

4.Push to github:
git push -u origin master

installing mongodb into cloud9
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
$ mkdir data
$ echo 'mongod --bind_ip=$IP --dbpath=data --nojournal --rest "$@"' > mongod
$ chmod a+x mongod
./mongod
